1. What is data type ? why do we have data types?

SQL Server supports two kinds of character data types: regular and Unicode.
 Regular data types  include CHAR and VARCHAR, and Unicode data types include
 NCHAR and NVARCHAR. Regular  characters use 1 byte of storage for each
 character, whereas Unicode data requires 2 bytes per character, and in cases
 in which a surrogate pair is needed, 4 bytes are require
